title: Stanwood man stabbed by neighbor
text:
A 42 year-old Stanwood man was stabbed in the chest Friday morning after a confrontation with his neighbor.
The victim and the attacker live on the same property in the 26200 block of Marine Drive, but in different homes.
Police said the victim was returning home on his bicycle about 1:45 a.m. when he was confronted by his neighbor in their shared driveway.
The victim said he was punched and stabbed by the 47-year-old man.
He was transported to Providence Regional Medical Center with serious injuries.
The attacker is expected to be booked into the Snohomish County jail later Friday.
